From [[Osco-Umbrian]], from {{etyl|itc-pro|la}} {{term/t|itc-pro|*lukʷos}}, metathesis of {{etyl|ine-pro|la}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*wĺ̥kʷos}}. Osco-Umbrian regularly has [[Proto-Indo-European]] */kʷ/ → /p/. Instead of expected {{term/t|la|*volpos}} (compare Latin {{term/t|la|*volquus}}), there is ''l''/''w'' metathesis, most likely to avoid conflation with {{term/t|la|volpēs||fox}}. Cognates include Ancient Greek {{term|λύκος|tr=lúkos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, Old English {{term|wulf|lang=ang}} (English {{term|wolf|lang=en}}) and Russian ''[[волк]]''.

